<div class="px-6 lg:px-16 py-6 w-full">
    <h2 class="text-gray-700 font-semibold text-3xl pt-6">About <span class="underline text-indigo-600 font-bold">Sentence</span></h2>
    <div class="w-3/3 md:w-2/3 text-gray-600">
        <p class="mb-2">Discover a new way to communicate!</p>
        <p class="mb-2">Sentence is a small web application that allows you to generate a playlist according to the sentence you have entered, you will then have the possibility to share it via a link or social networks.</p>
        <p class="mb-2">There are 2 modes, the first "Spotify view" will display the results found in a playlist (there may be holes if the music does not exist). And the second "Brut view" will complete these holes with fake music generated automatically (you wonâ€™t be able to generate the playlist afterwards, but make a screen).</p>
        <p class="mb-2">Sentence also generates the playlist on your Spotify account</p>
    </div>


    <h2 class="text-gray-700 font-semibold text-3xl pt-6">Privacy</h2>
    <div class="w-3/3 md:w-2/3 text-gray-600">
        <p class="mb-4">To use Sentence, you must link your Spotify account to the application (necessary to search system and creation of playlists directly on your account). We do not store any personal data.</p>
        <p class="mb-4 text-gray-800 font-medium underline">Here is a list of required scopes and their use :</p>
        <ul class="mb-4">
            <li class="flex"><span class="font-medium text-indigo-700"><i class="fa fa-caret-right"></i> basic</span> <span class="italic text-gray-600 ml-2">Access to your accound data (for login)</span> </li>
            <li class="flex"><span class="font-medium text-indigo-700"><i class="fa fa-caret-right"></i> <a href="https://developer.spotify.com/documentation/web-api/reference/playlists/create-playlist/" target="blank">playlist-modify-public</a></span> <span class="italic text-gray-600 ml-2">Create a playlist into your account</span> </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mb-4">If you are logged in with a wrong account or want to log out of the application click <a href="<%= BASE_URL %>/logout" class="text-red-700 hover:text-red-500 underline">here</a>. You can also remove Sentence access to your Spotify account by clicking <a href="https://www.spotify.com/fr/account/apps/" target="blank" class="text-red-700 hover:text-red-500 underline">here</a>.</p>
        <p class="mb-4">The sentences you generate in the application may be saved anonymously in the gallery if they contain no errors.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-gray-700 font-semibold text-3xl pt-6">Discover</h2>
    <div class="w-3/3 md:w-2/3 text-gray-600 pb-6">
        <p class="mb-2">Sentence is an <a href="https://github.com/Mikheull/Sentence" target="blank" class="text-indigo-700 hover:text-indigo-500 underline">open-source</a> project developed in Nodejs with the <a href="https://developer.spotify.com/documentation/web-api/" target="blank" class="text-indigo-700 hover:text-indigo-500 underline">Spotify API</a> and the wrapper "<a href="https://github.com/thelinmichael/spotify-web-api-node" target="blank" class="text-indigo-700 hover:text-indigo-500 underline">spotify-web-api-node</a>".</p>
    </div>
</div>